channel.title: Run.bat error with silabs new jar, nooby yes. But help please
channel.description:
Please do on flaming or spamming up the thread because I cannot do this self, I am intelligent when it comes to server coding how ever not when it comes jar files.
When I downloaded silabs latest jar in the client 6 post within the server downloads section here I attempted to run it using this code,
[code]@echo off JAVA -Xmx500m -jar silabclient-168-50-413363112-18-67-95.jar 0 0 highmem members 0[/code]
Then after that didn't work out, I used this one which is basically the same thing.
[code]JAVA -Xmx500m -jar silabclient-168-50-413363112-18-67-95.jar 0 0 highmem members 0 pause [/code]
Each time I got the error below in the run.bat,
[code]c:\Documents and Setting\******* ****\Desktop>JAVA -Xmx500m -jar silabclient-168-50-413363112-18-67-95.jar 0 0 highmem members 0
c:\Documents and Settings\******* ****\Desktop>pause Press any key to continue. . . [/code] Note: the *'s are my name. Don't want people knowing it.
So, If anyone could help me with this it would be great fully appreciated.[br][br][size=1]Posted on: December 13, 2007, 05:28:33 AM[/size][hr]Bump, its been over a day.
